Which four people ran for President in the 1860 election and who won?;Southern Democrat John C. Breckinridge favored a national law enforcing slavery. Northern Democrat Stephen Douglas wanted popular sovereignty as the solution to the slavery issue. Constitutional Unionist John Bell favored slavery, but did not demand a national law enforcing slavery. Republican Abraham Lincoln viewed slavery as immoral and was against its expansion. Results: Lincoln won the electoral vote, and Republicans won a majority in the Senate and House of Representatives.
